1
00:01:29,350 --> 00:01:31,341
There was no one like Hal.

2
00:01:31,553 --> 00:01:34,147
He met me at a party
and swept me off my feet.

3
00:01:34,355 --> 00:01:35,845
"Blue Moon" was the song
that was playing.

4
00:01:36,057 --> 00:01:37,547
- You know "Blue Moon?"
- Sure.

5
00:01:37,759 --> 00:01:39,989
I still remember that.

6
00:01:41,963 --> 00:01:45,228
And one more year
and I would have graduated.

7
00:01:45,466 --> 00:01:49,266
But I quit BU to marry him. I mean,
what was I learning at school anyway?

8
00:01:49,504 --> 00:01:53,030
I mean, can you picture me
as an anthropologist?

9
00:01:54,575 --> 00:01:56,065
Is that a joke?

10
00:01:56,276 --> 00:01:59,609
The sex was always great. Well,
he was nine years older than me.

11
00:01:59,846 --> 00:02:01,837
He'd already made
and lost a fortune.

12
00:02:02,049 --> 00:02:05,075
But then he made it back, and more.
I mean, much more.

13
00:02:05,285 --> 00:02:06,582
God, he was dynamic.

14
00:02:06,787 --> 00:02:09,517
Taught me everything I know
about real lovemaking...

15
00:02:09,723 --> 00:02:11,918
...not that I care
to get too graphic.

16
00:02:12,125 --> 00:02:15,356
Believe me when I tell you.
They tried six medications on me.

17
00:02:15,562 --> 00:02:17,189
Cocktails, they call them.

18
00:02:17,397 --> 00:02:19,991
The only cocktail that helped
was a Stoli martini.

19
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:21,428
I never trusted doctors.

20
00:02:21,635 --> 00:02:24,263
Doctors put both my parents
in early graves.

21
00:02:24,504 --> 00:02:26,301
I have never been
to San Francisco.

22
00:02:26,540 --> 00:02:29,532
And Hal and I traveled everywhere.
I hear it's beautiful.

23
00:02:29,743 --> 00:02:32,576
I'll be staying with my sister, Ginger.
She's divorced.

24
00:02:32,779 --> 00:02:37,010
Biologically, she's not my sister.
She's adopted. We're both adopted.

25
00:02:37,216 --> 00:02:39,946
I couldn't stand her ex-husband.
He used to hit her.

26
00:02:40,152 --> 00:02:42,120
That's mine. The Vuitton.

27
00:02:42,321 --> 00:02:45,222
My plan is to start
a new life out here.

28
00:02:45,424 --> 00:02:48,052
Put everything behind me
and start fresh.

29
00:02:48,261 --> 00:02:52,459
Go West. Was it Horace Greeley
who said that? "Go West."

30
00:02:52,665 --> 00:02:55,964
Oh, there's my family.
It was really nice talking to you.

31
00:02:56,168 --> 00:02:58,762
Oh, I'll call you, maybe for lunch.

32
00:02:58,971 --> 00:03:01,303
I don't have your number.

33
00:03:02,074 --> 00:03:06,340
- Who's that woman you were talking to?
- I was sitting next to her on the plane.

34
00:03:06,579 --> 00:03:07,978
She was talking to herself.

35
00:03:08,180 --> 00:03:10,842
I thought she said something to me.
I said, "What?"

36
00:03:11,083 --> 00:03:14,075
But she couldn't stop babbling
about her life.

37
00:03:31,269 --> 00:03:33,760
Where...?
Where am I exactly?

38
00:03:33,972 --> 00:03:37,169
You said 305 South Van Ness.

39
00:03:43,148 --> 00:03:46,379
- Can you wait, help me with my bags?
- Sure.

40
00:03:51,656 --> 00:03:54,147
I don't know where she is.

41
00:03:54,392 --> 00:03:56,587
She expected me.

42
00:03:57,128 --> 00:03:59,722
The plane was on time.

43
00:04:06,337 --> 00:04:07,702
- Yes, I'm...
- You all right?

44
00:04:07,905 --> 00:04:11,864
I'm fine. I just sometimes get
where I can't take a deep breath...

45
00:04:12,109 --> 00:04:16,978
...and when I can, it makes me panic
and it makes it even worse.

46
00:04:17,181 --> 00:04:18,842
Okay.

47
00:04:20,617 --> 00:04:23,108
- Could I have some privacy?
- Sure, sure.

48
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:25,049
Hello, Ginger?

49
00:04:25,255 --> 00:04:27,723
Yes, I'm here.
I'm right in front of the place.

50
00:04:27,925 --> 00:04:30,052
It is 305?

51
00:04:32,763 --> 00:04:34,924
Well, how long?

52
00:04:35,232 --> 00:04:38,224
What?
Where is it?

53
00:04:38,435 --> 00:04:41,927
No, no, I see it.
Okay. Oh, okay.

54
00:04:42,172 --> 00:04:45,630
Just- Would you please hurry?
My sister left the keys in the bar.

55
00:04:45,843 --> 00:04:47,776
- Can you wait?
- Sure!

56
00:05:10,433 --> 00:05:12,060
Is that it?

57
00:05:15,605 --> 00:05:17,368
Thank you.

58
00:05:18,441 --> 00:05:20,272
Oh, thank you.

59
00:05:20,476 --> 00:05:23,468
Have a great day, all right?
Bye-bye.

60
00:05:28,184 --> 00:05:30,481
- So, what do you think?
- I love it.

61
00:05:30,719 --> 00:05:33,620
The fireplaces work.
I don't like when they're for show.

62
00:05:33,822 --> 00:05:36,620
It's so light and airy
and the ceilings are so high.

63
00:05:36,825 --> 00:05:39,692
How can anyone breathe
with a low ceiling? The view...

64
00:05:39,895 --> 00:05:42,455
- You wanted Fifth Avenue.
- Central Park. Superb.

65
00:05:42,697 --> 00:05:44,392
Oh, this space is perfect.

66
00:05:44,599 --> 00:05:46,294
We hardly have to do a thing.

67
00:05:46,501 --> 00:05:48,833
- You shouldn't spoil me so.
- Well, why not?

68
00:05:49,070 --> 00:05:51,630
Who else am I gonna spoil?
Did I tell you my news?

69
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:53,967
- What?
- Danny is gonna be living with us.

70
00:05:54,209 --> 00:05:56,234
Oh, honey.
Oh, that's great news.

71
00:05:56,445 --> 00:05:58,606
I worked it out with his mom,
her lawyers.

72
00:05:58,814 --> 00:06:03,012
Oh, he'll be so much happier
when he's with us full-time.

73
00:06:05,020 --> 00:06:07,215
Happy birthday, Danny.

74
00:06:07,823 --> 00:06:11,623
Kids at school say we're really rich
and that you give money to charity.

75
00:06:11,827 --> 00:06:14,659
Sure I do. You gotta remember
as you go through life...

76
00:06:14,862 --> 00:06:17,592
...to share what you earn
with the less fortunate.

77
00:06:17,798 --> 00:06:20,494
Not everyone is as
lucky as we are.

78
00:06:20,734 --> 00:06:21,826
- Domingo?
- Yes, ma'am.

79
00:06:22,036 --> 00:06:24,800
- Another bottle of the Margaux.
- Sure.

80
00:06:25,239 --> 00:06:26,263
Excuse me.

81
00:06:26,474 --> 00:06:28,840
- It would look perfect.
- Wouldn't wash me out?

82
00:06:29,043 --> 00:06:30,772
No, not at all. Not the way he...

83
00:06:30,978 --> 00:06:33,640
Oh, isn't he sweet?

84
00:06:33,848 --> 00:06:37,249
This song was playing
when Hal and I first met.

85
00:06:37,952 --> 00:06:41,513
- I fell in love with the name Jasmine.
- Oh, so romantic.

86
00:06:42,189 --> 00:06:44,350
I changed it.

87
00:06:44,558 --> 00:06:47,891
Yeah, Jeanette had no panache.

88
00:06:50,898 --> 00:06:53,264
This song was playing
when we first met.

89
00:06:53,467 --> 00:06:57,493
You know it? Yeah, we met
at a party at Martha's Vineyard.

90
00:06:58,004 --> 00:06:59,904
"Blue Moon."

91
00:07:00,874 --> 00:07:02,865
Come on, boys.

92
00:07:03,643 --> 00:07:07,170
Okay, let's go, Augie.
I gotta get home. Someone's waiting.

93
00:07:07,380 --> 00:07:09,371
We helped Dad
move the furniture today.

94
00:07:09,582 --> 00:07:12,278
Oh, really? That's your idea
of taking the boys?

95
00:07:12,485 --> 00:07:15,386
Letting them help you lug
somebody's furniture upstairs?

96
00:07:15,588 --> 00:07:17,556
- They loved it. Great exercise.
- Yeah?

97
00:07:17,790 --> 00:07:20,520
- They-- We ate franks and beans.
- Yeah.

98
00:07:20,727 --> 00:07:23,560
- Relax.
- Okay. Let's go, Johnny, come on.

99
00:07:23,796 --> 00:07:26,560
- Come on. Let's go. Come on.
- What's the rush?

100
00:07:26,799 --> 00:07:28,994
What's the rush, Ginger?
You got a date?

101
00:07:29,202 --> 00:07:30,669
It's none of your business.

102
00:07:30,870 --> 00:07:34,169
- It happens to be Jeanette, so...
- Jeanette?

103
00:07:34,374 --> 00:07:36,239
Jasmine?
What is she doing in town?

104
00:07:36,442 --> 00:07:39,172
She's living with me
till she gets back on her feet.

105
00:07:39,379 --> 00:07:41,074
She's had a bad time. Yeah.

106
00:07:41,313 --> 00:07:44,043
When she had money,
she wanted nothing to do with you.

107
00:07:44,249 --> 00:07:46,240
Now that she's broke,
she's moving in.

108
00:07:46,451 --> 00:07:48,442
She's not just broke.
She's screwed up.

109
00:07:48,687 --> 00:07:51,212
And it's none of your damn
business. She's family.

110
00:07:51,423 --> 00:07:52,913
- She stole our money.
- Okay.

111
00:07:53,125 --> 00:07:57,255
Understand? We could have been set.
That was our whole chance in life.

112
00:07:57,462 --> 00:08:01,558
For the last time, Augie,
he was the crook, not her, okay?

113
00:08:01,767 --> 00:08:03,894
What the hell did she know
about finance?

114
00:08:04,102 --> 00:08:07,902
Don't stand there and tell me that.
She's married to a guy for years...

115
00:08:08,106 --> 00:08:10,939
...up to his ass in phony real
estate and bank fraud.

116
00:08:11,143 --> 00:08:12,770
She knew nothing about it?

117
00:08:12,978 --> 00:08:16,573
Believe me, she knew, Ginger.
Okay? She knew.

118
00:08:16,782 --> 00:08:19,774
But when all those diamonds
and minks were flying in...

119
00:08:19,985 --> 00:08:23,113
- ... she just looked the other way.
- I don't think so, Augie.

120
00:08:23,355 --> 00:08:28,621
You said it. You said to me,
"She's a phony and had to know."

121
00:08:28,859 --> 00:08:32,056
Jasmine, your country house
is so beautiful.

122
00:08:32,263 --> 00:08:32,789
See?

123
00:08:32,815 --> 00:08:34,916
I'm sorry, but we need
an answer on this.

124
00:08:35,099 --> 00:08:37,761
I told you, you change the
name of the corporation.

125
00:08:37,969 --> 00:08:41,063
- Operate under Global Innovations.
- I don't know if we can.

126
00:08:41,272 --> 00:08:42,603
I think we can, actually.

127
00:08:42,807 --> 00:08:45,435
- Pay out of the accounts in Amsterdam.
- Amsterdam.

128
00:08:45,643 --> 00:08:49,443
Whenever I hear them, they're one
step ahead of the Justice Department.

129
00:08:49,647 --> 00:08:51,478
Just hope your
house is not bugged.

130
00:08:51,682 --> 00:08:54,515
Oh, I never pay attention
to Hal's business affairs.

131
00:08:54,752 --> 00:08:56,743
I have no head for
that sort of thing.

132
00:08:56,954 --> 00:09:00,321
- We transfer to the old corporation?
- We could. Perfectly legal.

133
00:09:00,524 --> 00:09:04,790
- It would be a mistake under that name.
- Definitely get in trouble for that.

134
00:09:04,996 --> 00:09:07,191
Just don't file a joint tax return.

135
00:09:07,431 --> 00:09:11,093
Don't say that. I sign anything.
I'm very trusting.

136
00:09:11,301 --> 00:09:12,632
Famous last words.

137
00:09:12,836 --> 00:09:15,202
It's called looking the other way.

138
00:09:17,540 --> 00:09:20,304
Jasmine.
Oh, my God.

139
00:09:20,510 --> 00:09:22,478
- Look at you.
- Look at you.

140
00:09:22,679 --> 00:09:25,113
Oh, I am so sorry for the wait.

141
00:09:25,315 --> 00:09:27,510
- Sorry, I think I'm in Paris.
- It's okay.

142
00:09:27,717 --> 00:09:30,015
- No, it's fine.
- Augie's day with the boys.

143
00:09:30,220 --> 00:09:31,983
Well, no wonder you're late.

144
00:09:32,188 --> 00:09:33,917
- Hello. Matthew, is it?
- Yeah.

145
00:09:34,124 --> 00:09:36,684
Boys, say hello.
I told you about her, remember?

146
00:09:36,926 --> 00:09:39,360
- Hi, I'm Jasmine.
- Shake hands. Okay, go play.

147
00:09:39,562 --> 00:09:40,995
- They're big.
- I know.

148
00:09:41,197 --> 00:09:43,324
- I'm getting it first.
- Quiet, you two.

149
00:09:43,533 --> 00:09:46,161
- Well, they're loud.
- Stop running around.

150
00:09:46,369 --> 00:09:49,133
Christ, this kid's got...
What the hell is it? ADD?

151
00:09:49,339 --> 00:09:53,798
- Yeah. Your place is homey.
- Are you kidding me?

152
00:09:54,009 --> 00:09:57,536
No, I mean, it"s got a very...
Well, it's casual charm.

153
00:09:57,746 --> 00:10:00,442
God, knock it off, Jasmine.

154
00:10:01,383 --> 00:10:05,149
I need to stay here
for a while. No, I do.

155
00:10:05,721 --> 00:10:07,746
- I'm out of cash.
- Okay.

156
00:10:07,990 --> 00:10:10,686
Couldn't pay my rent in Brooklyn.
Can you believe...

157
00:10:10,893 --> 00:10:13,885
...I had to move out of my home,
take a place in Brooklyn?

158
00:10:14,096 --> 00:10:17,190
But I'm dead broke. Really,
the government took everything.

159
00:10:17,399 --> 00:10:19,060
And the lawyers.

160
00:10:19,268 --> 00:10:20,895
And I can't be alone, Ginger.

161
00:10:21,103 --> 00:10:23,697
I really get some bad thoughts
when I'm alone.

162
00:10:23,906 --> 00:10:27,398
Well, you know, all I can say is,
you look great.

163
00:10:28,510 --> 00:10:30,876
- Now who's lying?
- You do.

164
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:33,913
You know, I was up all last night.
I was so anxious...

165
00:10:34,116 --> 00:10:35,606
- ... about moving here.
- Yeah?

166
00:10:35,851 --> 00:10:39,547
- I wasn't sure how angry you still were.
- Oh, well...

167
00:10:40,788 --> 00:10:43,621
- Another drink? We're celebrating.
- Of course, yeah.

168
00:10:43,858 --> 00:10:46,088
Oh, the flight was bumpy.

169
00:10:46,294 --> 00:10:50,424
I didn't eat anything on the plane.
Oh, the food was awful. Here it is.

170
00:10:50,631 --> 00:10:53,498
I mean, you'd think
first class, right?

171
00:10:54,035 --> 00:10:55,559
You flew first class?

172
00:10:55,770 --> 00:10:58,500
I don't know how anyone puts up
with those airlines.

173
00:10:58,706 --> 00:11:02,403
- Isn't first class a fortune?
- Yes, I was quite shocked.

174
00:11:02,610 --> 00:11:06,546
- I thought you were tapped out.
- I'm worse than tapped out, baby.

175
00:11:06,748 --> 00:11:08,943
I've run up some serious debts.

176
00:11:09,150 --> 00:11:10,947
So how did you fly first class?

177
00:11:11,152 --> 00:11:15,020
I don't know, Ginger.
I just did.

178
00:11:15,723 --> 00:11:18,954
All I meant was, if you've got
no money, to go first class...

179
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:21,957
You know me.
I splurge from habit.

180
00:11:23,163 --> 00:11:26,223
Would you stop staring
at my luggage?

181
00:11:26,433 --> 00:11:28,594
Yes, it's Louis Vuitton.

182
00:11:29,035 --> 00:11:32,471
- You told me you had to sell everything.
- Look, look, look.

183
00:11:32,672 --> 00:11:36,472
These are used, old suitcases.
See, with my initials. Who'd want them?

184
00:11:36,676 --> 00:11:40,043
I sold what jewels and furs
I could hide from Uncle Sam.

185
00:11:40,247 --> 00:11:42,078
God, I hate to tell
you about that.

186
00:11:42,282 --> 00:11:46,548
Jewelry is priceless, a great investment
when you buy it at Graff or Van Cleef...

187
00:11:46,753 --> 00:11:49,745
...until you're desperate for money
and forced to sell...

188
00:11:49,956 --> 00:11:52,550
...and then it seems
you can't give it away.

189
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:56,961
Kids, stop it, come on!

190
00:11:57,497 --> 00:11:59,931
- Were you adopted?
- Yes.

191
00:12:00,133 --> 00:12:01,964
We were both adopted.

192
00:12:02,169 --> 00:12:05,831
Born to different moms and dads,
but raised by the same mom and dad.

193
00:12:06,071 --> 00:12:08,665
Could you stop doing that
gun thing? Sorry.

194
00:12:08,874 --> 00:12:11,934
- Got migraine from the pressurized cabin.
- Matthew.

195
00:12:12,144 --> 00:12:14,271
Did you like the new mom and dad?

196
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:16,448
- Yes, of course...
- Aunt Jasmine did.

197
00:12:16,649 --> 00:12:19,812
I ran away from home
as fast as my feet could carry me.

198
00:12:20,019 --> 00:12:22,010
- How come?
- Well...

199
00:12:22,221 --> 00:12:24,689
Our mother liked Aunt Jasmine
and not me.

200
00:12:24,890 --> 00:12:26,983
- Oh, stop.
- How come?

201
00:12:27,193 --> 00:12:29,525
- She had better genes.
- Don't tell them that.

202
00:12:29,728 --> 00:12:33,186
- Well, am I lying?
- Dad said you're glad we lived far away.

203
00:12:33,399 --> 00:12:35,167
What?

204
00:12:35,234 --> 00:12:38,795
They're perfect for the dress
that I'm wearing to the Met Gala.

205
00:12:40,739 --> 00:12:43,537
What's the matter?
Your mind is a million miles away.

206
00:12:43,742 --> 00:12:48,701
Oh, I'm sorry. No, I...
I just got a call from my sister, Ginger.

207
00:12:48,913 --> 00:12:53,213
Oh, God, she's coming to New York
for a week with her husband, Augie.

208
00:12:53,418 --> 00:12:54,885
He is a piece of work.

209
00:12:55,119 --> 00:12:57,679
I just... I don't know,
I guess I have to see them.

210
00:12:57,889 --> 00:13:00,255
- The one in San Francisco, the builder?
- Yeah.

211
00:13:00,491 --> 00:13:04,154
Oh, no, he's a contractor.
I mean, he's... No, he's a handyman.

212
00:13:04,362 --> 00:13:07,490
No, don't get me wrong.
I love Ginger, I do. She's a dear.

213
00:13:07,699 --> 00:13:10,634
But our paths just went
in totally different directions.

214
00:13:10,835 --> 00:13:11,893
Okay, that happens.

215
00:13:12,136 --> 00:13:15,128
It's terrible of me to say,
but she was never too bright.

216
00:13:15,340 --> 00:13:18,776
You know? And she was so wild
and I, of course, was Miss Perfect.

217
00:13:20,778 --> 00:13:22,678
- Hi.
- Oh, you made it.

218
00:13:22,881 --> 00:13:24,906
- How lovely to see you.
- Hi. Oh, my God.

219
00:13:25,149 --> 00:13:26,707
- Welcome.
- Hi. Thank you.

220
00:13:26,918 --> 00:13:29,079
- Oh, this is my husband, Augie.
- Augie.

221
00:13:29,287 --> 00:13:31,447
- This is Jeanette.
- Jasmine. I changed it.

222
00:13:31,688 --> 00:13:34,248
- Jasmine.
- I'm finally getting to meet the sister.

223
00:13:34,458 --> 00:13:38,360
I know. Hello. I'm so sorry
we couldn't make it to the wedding.

224
00:13:38,562 --> 00:13:41,053
Just that Hal had some business
in Saint-Tropez.

225
00:13:41,265 --> 00:13:43,256
- Couldn't get back in time.
- Know what?

226
00:13:43,467 --> 00:13:46,903
You missed a nice little party.
My friend Dennis sang.

227
00:13:47,104 --> 00:13:49,595
- He's great. Dennis Rackabuto.
- I know. Hey...

228
00:13:49,806 --> 00:13:52,468
Hal! You remember Ginger.

229
00:13:52,709 --> 00:13:54,074
- Oh, my gosh.
- How are you?

230
00:13:54,278 --> 00:13:55,768
- How are you?
- This is Augie.

231
00:13:55,979 --> 00:13:57,674
- Augie. How you doing?
- Awesome.

232
00:13:57,881 --> 00:13:59,781
- Hell of a place you got.
- Thank you.

233
00:13:59,983 --> 00:14:01,883
- Why don't you come through?
- Told you.

234
00:14:02,085 --> 00:14:03,950
- Yvette, coffee?
- This is really...

235
00:14:04,187 --> 00:14:05,313
Yeah, she's got taste.

236
00:14:05,555 --> 00:14:07,489
It's like what you
see in the movies.

237
00:14:07,724 --> 00:14:11,455
We have so much to catch up on.
Can't wait for you to show us New York.

238
00:14:11,695 --> 00:14:13,686
Why don't you take
our car and driver?

239
00:14:13,897 --> 00:14:17,127
Well, I hope you're gonna come.
I mean, how often am I here?

240
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:20,080
No, no, I will definitely
make some time.

241
00:14:20,106 --> 00:14:21,021
Oh, good.

242
00:14:23,139 --> 00:14:24,299
Where are you staying?

243
00:14:24,507 --> 00:14:27,999
Oh, well, we... We thought about
asking if we could stay with you...

244
00:14:28,244 --> 00:14:31,645
...but we don't wanna impose,
so we got a room at the Marriott.

245
00:14:31,847 --> 00:14:33,712
- Oh, the Marriott's perfect.
- Yeah.

246
00:14:33,916 --> 00:14:36,908
I'll have my office contact them
and forward us the bill.

247
00:14:37,119 --> 00:14:39,314
- Oh, no.
- No, no, no, it's not necessary.

248
00:14:39,522 --> 00:14:41,649
Please, you're our guests.
I insist.

249
00:14:41,857 --> 00:14:45,293
Oh, well, then we insist
on taking you two to dinner tonight.

250
00:14:45,861 --> 00:14:48,830
- What? Tonight?
- Yeah.

251
00:14:49,098 --> 00:14:51,623
We have dinner plans.

252
00:14:51,834 --> 00:14:54,769
I don't think we can...
Something we can't get out of.

253
00:14:54,971 --> 00:14:56,461
- I'm sorry.
- There'll be time.

254
00:14:56,672 --> 00:14:59,970
We stashed the kids with Augie's
sister, we're here for a week.

255
00:15:00,175 --> 00:15:02,006
- It's gonna be great.
- It is. Okay.

256
00:15:02,243 --> 00:15:04,768
Well, we don't have
a lot of free time...

257
00:15:04,980 --> 00:15:07,881
...but we'll definitely take you
to Le Cirque, won't we?

258
00:15:08,116 --> 00:15:09,515
I mean, or Daniel. I mean...

259
00:15:09,751 --> 00:15:12,515
- They'd get a kick out of that.
- Yeah, absolutely.

260
00:15:12,754 --> 00:15:16,986
I know your birthday is this week.
Let us at least take you out for that.

261
00:15:18,793 --> 00:15:22,524
- I love how you're doing your hair.
- Oh, thanks.

262
00:15:22,764 --> 00:15:26,996
You'll have to take me shopping.
You always could pick clothes.

263
00:15:28,770 --> 00:15:31,364
And Augie's got
some exciting business news...

264
00:15:31,573 --> 00:15:33,700
...he wants to talk to Hal about.

265
00:15:33,908 --> 00:15:36,775
Don't worry, I don't need
to borrow money. We're flush.

266
00:15:36,978 --> 00:15:39,173
- Yeah, - What kind of
work do you do, Augie?

267
00:15:39,381 --> 00:15:42,713
Well, you know, I do, like,
repairs, furniture moving...

268
00:15:42,916 --> 00:15:44,907
...but I got plans
to be my own boss.

269
00:15:45,152 --> 00:15:47,814
We'll talk about it over dinner.
They're going out.

270
00:15:48,022 --> 00:15:49,421
Hey, could we have a tour?

271
00:15:49,656 --> 00:15:53,888
Oh, yeah, of course.
Why don't you start in the kitchen?

272
00:15:54,094 --> 00:15:57,188
- Is there a little girls' room?
- Just down the hall.

273
00:15:58,599 --> 00:16:00,157
Five days.

274
00:16:00,367 --> 00:16:03,063
I'll have to invite them
to my birthday party now.

275
00:16:03,303 --> 00:16:07,069
- Where did she come up with him?
- I always feel so guilty around Ginger.

276
00:16:07,307 --> 00:16:10,071
We've got to make sure
we make their stay extra nice.

277
00:16:10,310 --> 00:16:13,302
My God, five days.

278
00:16:15,549 --> 00:16:17,517
Look.

279
00:16:18,452 --> 00:16:21,216
It's so beautiful.

280
00:16:21,422 --> 00:16:23,413
Oh, but where would I wear
a Fendi bag?

281
00:16:23,624 --> 00:16:25,819
Oh, go ahead.
It's my treat.

282
00:16:26,026 --> 00:16:28,118
- No.
- Yeah.

283
00:16:28,361 --> 00:16:30,056
Really?

284
00:16:30,263 --> 00:16:33,357
Oh, my God.
I love it. Look.

285
00:16:33,566 --> 00:16:34,760
Look.

286
00:16:34,967 --> 00:16:37,765
- Take the other one off.
- No, I like this.

287
00:16:39,939 --> 00:16:43,875
Boy, this is some
place you got here.

288
00:16:44,077 --> 00:16:46,375
- I mean, this is unreal.
- It is.

289
00:16:46,579 --> 00:16:48,342
Reminds me of when I was a kid.

290
00:16:48,548 --> 00:16:49,947
I used to be a lifeguard.

291
00:16:50,149 --> 00:16:52,777
Start your own construction company?
Great idea.

292
00:16:52,985 --> 00:16:55,453
- We came into some money.
- Tell him how, Augie.

293
00:16:58,157 --> 00:17:01,718
Well, the first 10, 12,000,
I really worked for.

294
00:17:01,928 --> 00:17:03,555
Put away a little each week.

295
00:17:03,763 --> 00:17:05,754
But he's not telling
you the big news.

296
00:17:05,965 --> 00:17:08,058
- Why we're in New York.
- You tell them.

297
00:17:08,267 --> 00:17:10,291
Okay, I will.

298
00:17:10,502 --> 00:17:11,992
We always play the lottery...

299
00:17:12,237 --> 00:17:15,434
...and we never even get two numbers.
Am I right?

300
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:17,130
But last week, we hit it.

301
00:17:17,375 --> 00:17:19,240
We got 200,000 bucks.

302
00:17:19,444 --> 00:17:21,810
Oh, that's fantastic.

303
00:17:22,013 --> 00:17:24,072
- I thought I'd drop dead.
- That's great.

304
00:17:24,282 --> 00:17:27,308
I never held that kind of money
in my hands. I mean, ever.

305
00:17:27,519 --> 00:17:29,111
He was shaking when we won.

306
00:17:29,321 --> 00:17:33,314
Me? You had to see her. I had to tell
her, this is a once-in-a-lifetime.

307
00:17:33,525 --> 00:17:35,152
- Congratulations.
- Yeah.

308
00:17:35,393 --> 00:17:38,487
He wants to begin a business.
What do you think?

309
00:17:38,697 --> 00:17:43,259
Well, if you like, I think Hal
could probably help you do better.

310
00:17:43,468 --> 00:17:44,492
Yeah?

311
00:17:44,703 --> 00:17:49,333
You know-- You know, I'm no gambler.
I mean, not with my one chance to-

312
00:17:49,541 --> 00:17:53,637
Hey, come on. We don't know the first
thing about money, but he does.

313
00:17:53,844 --> 00:17:57,211
First thing is how not to give half
your money to the government.

314
00:17:57,448 --> 00:18:00,315
Look, I know there's taxes,
but, I mean, what can I do?

315
00:18:00,518 --> 00:18:02,679
- There are ways.
- You see, Augie? You see?

316
00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:06,549
Suppose I put you in a venture that
was low-risk, but very high-yield.

317
00:18:06,790 --> 00:18:10,317
I'm not talking about 6 or 7 percent.
I'm talking about 20 percent.

318
00:18:10,528 --> 00:18:12,189
- Profitable enough?
-20 percent?

319
00:18:12,429 --> 00:18:15,193
He's developing a group of hotels
in the Caribbean.

320
00:18:15,432 --> 00:18:18,526
You mean,
not starting my own business.

321
00:18:18,736 --> 00:18:21,034
No, we mean investing with Hal.

322
00:18:21,238 --> 00:18:24,366
Jeez, investing what?
You mean the whole thing?

323
00:18:24,575 --> 00:18:27,009
You need money to make money.
Am I right?

324
00:18:27,244 --> 00:18:28,302
Ginger.

325
00:18:28,512 --> 00:18:31,379
Let them in on one of your-
The hotel deal or something.

326
00:18:31,582 --> 00:18:33,812
It'd be great for them.
Make a killing.

327
00:18:34,018 --> 00:18:37,054
- Pay attention, Augie.
- I'm paying attention.

328
00:18:38,087 --> 00:18:40,146
You will make money for them,
won't you?

329
00:18:40,356 --> 00:18:42,153
I make money, they make money.

330
00:18:42,358 --> 00:18:44,155
God, they're hard work.

331
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:46,385
Tomorrow I'm taking the day off.

332
00:18:46,596 --> 00:18:49,588
I've neglected everything,
my yoga, my Pilates.

333
00:18:49,832 --> 00:18:51,561
I've got that luncheon to plan...

334
00:18:51,768 --> 00:18:54,498
...the fundraiser
for the Central Park Conservancy.

335
00:18:54,704 --> 00:18:56,865
I've rented them a
limo and a driver...

336
00:18:57,073 --> 00:19:00,600
...and I've suggested they go
to the South Street Seaport.

337
00:19:01,044 --> 00:19:03,706
Can you imagine if they lived here?

338
00:19:05,548 --> 00:19:08,073
Here, for doing your duty.

339
00:19:08,284 --> 00:19:10,218
Happy birthday.

340
00:19:11,054 --> 00:19:15,081
I'm giving it to you now so you can
wear it to your party tomorrow night.

341
00:19:15,558 --> 00:19:19,085
Oh, sweetheart, it's beautiful.

342
00:19:19,295 --> 00:19:22,752
Not bad taste
for a philistine businessman, huh?

343
00:20:54,954 --> 00:20:58,117
- I know, it's so extravagant.
- Oh, look at that.

344
00:20:58,325 --> 00:21:00,850
He surprised me in the tub,
so to speak.

345
00:21:01,094 --> 00:21:04,860
Corsica's a bore. The weather's nice,
but it's nothing like Sardinia.

346
00:21:05,098 --> 00:21:08,397
This year you are coming
to Palm Beach, no excuses.

347
00:21:09,536 --> 00:21:12,198
- Hey, Jasmine.
- What?

348
00:21:12,405 --> 00:21:14,839
- Who's that woman?
- Which?

349
00:21:15,041 --> 00:21:16,531
- That one.
- Oh, Raylene.

350
00:21:16,743 --> 00:21:18,836
She's a friend. I love Raylene.

351
00:21:19,045 --> 00:21:20,706
We met in a yoga class.

352
00:21:20,914 --> 00:21:22,677
- Isn't she pretty?
- Yeah.

353
00:21:22,882 --> 00:21:24,645
She runs a modeling agency.

354
00:21:24,851 --> 00:21:27,251
- How long have you known her?
- Few years. Why?

355
00:21:27,821 --> 00:21:30,756
- And you trust her?
- Trust her?

356
00:21:30,990 --> 00:21:34,425
Of course I trust her.
What kind of question is that?

357
00:21:34,660 --> 00:21:37,322
She just seems so cozy all night
with your husband.

358
00:21:37,529 --> 00:21:40,930
I wouldn't worry. Hal's not
the roving type, nor is Raylene.

359
00:21:41,166 --> 00:21:43,657
- She's a very close friend.
- I don't know.

360
00:21:43,869 --> 00:21:46,201
If it was my husband,
I'd keep an eye on him.

361
00:21:46,405 --> 00:21:50,341
Goodness, you are a suspicious one.

362
00:21:50,542 --> 00:21:52,237
- I'm just saying.
- Just relax.

363
00:21:52,444 --> 00:21:54,435
I am relaxed.

364
00:21:55,547 --> 00:21:57,742
You shouldn't drink so much, Augie.

365
00:21:57,950 --> 00:22:01,386
Nobody wants to hear
those stupid Polish jokes, you know?

366
00:22:01,587 --> 00:22:03,578
Oh, I had a drink?

367
00:22:03,789 --> 00:22:04,847
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

368
00:22:05,057 --> 00:22:09,960
Let me tell you, you were half in
the bag the entire night, okay?

369
00:22:10,195 --> 00:22:12,288
Tell me about my drinking.

370
00:22:12,531 --> 00:22:15,932
- Give me that.
- What's eating you?

371
00:22:16,235 --> 00:22:20,694
If you saw your friend's wife kissing
another guy, would you tell your friend?

372
00:22:20,905 --> 00:22:22,702
- What?
- Would you tell your friend?

373
00:22:22,907 --> 00:22:25,171
- I'm talking.
- Tell him what?

374
00:22:26,811 --> 00:22:28,472
Are you listening to me?

375
00:22:28,713 --> 00:22:33,173
If you saw your friend's wife kissing
another guy, would you tell your friend?

376
00:22:33,384 --> 00:22:34,749
- Would you tell him?
- Yeah.

377
00:22:34,952 --> 00:22:38,046
- Bet your ass I'd tell him.
- But what if it causes trouble?

378
00:22:38,256 --> 00:22:39,689
Or maybe a divorce?

379
00:22:39,891 --> 00:22:42,985
If you don't say anything,
it could've been a passing thing.

380
00:22:43,227 --> 00:22:45,889
He never knows and he lives on
happy with his wife.

381
00:22:46,097 --> 00:22:49,794
You know, I would tell him,
because that's what a friend's for.

382
00:22:50,001 --> 00:22:52,970
You gotta have his back.
That's why I'd tell him.

383
00:22:53,204 --> 00:22:55,968
It's a tough call, Augie.
I don't know.

384
00:22:57,475 --> 00:22:58,965
- Ginger?
- What?

385
00:22:59,210 --> 00:23:01,643
What are we doing?
Are we playing charades?

386
00:23:01,845 --> 00:23:03,312
I mean, come on.

387
00:23:03,513 --> 00:23:05,981
- Did you see something?
- Yeah.

388
00:23:06,216 --> 00:23:08,707
On the street, by accident.

389
00:23:08,919 --> 00:23:12,912
I saw Hal kissing that brunette
who was at the party.

390
00:23:13,523 --> 00:23:17,983
You saw Hal kiss Raylene? Raylene?

391
00:23:18,228 --> 00:23:20,253
You know her name too?

392
00:23:20,597 --> 00:23:22,292
My God, she gets around.

393
00:23:22,499 --> 00:23:25,832
Oh, we were introduced. Come on,
you got nothing to worry about.

394
00:23:26,036 --> 00:23:28,231
- Yeah.
- Nobody could ever take your place.

395
00:23:28,438 --> 00:23:32,272
Yeah, believe me,
I wasn't thinking she'd look at you.

396
00:23:32,542 --> 00:23:34,976
- Nobody would ever look at me, right?
- Right.

397
00:23:35,178 --> 00:23:39,046
- You looked at me.
- Yeah, once. It was a mistake.

398
00:23:39,549 --> 00:23:42,848
- All right, listen.
- What?

399
00:23:43,053 --> 00:23:45,384
You think Hal's banging her?

400
00:23:45,988 --> 00:23:48,149
When Jasmine don't wanna
know something...

401
00:23:48,357 --> 00:23:51,326
...she's got a habit
of looking the other way.

402
00:23:51,527 --> 00:23:54,758
Thank you for my present.
I got so many comments.

403
00:23:54,964 --> 00:23:58,263
I think everyone enjoyed themselves
and that piano player was-

404
00:23:58,467 --> 00:24:00,958
He was fantastic. I got his card.

405
00:24:01,170 --> 00:24:05,197
What were you talking to Raylene
so intensely about?

406
00:24:05,407 --> 00:24:09,309
Oh, her husband is thinking about
getting his own plane.

407
00:24:09,512 --> 00:24:14,313
I was just weighing the pros and cons
for her of a Challenger versus a-

408
00:24:14,517 --> 00:24:17,145
- Gulfstream?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

409
00:24:17,820 --> 00:24:19,913
- She's so pretty.
- Yeah.

410
00:24:20,155 --> 00:24:23,386
Bill's out of town for a couple weeks
and she'll be all alone.

411
00:24:23,592 --> 00:24:27,789
I thought maybe we could take her out
to dinner or have her over here.

412
00:24:28,229 --> 00:24:29,787
- Yeah.
- Great.

413
00:24:29,998 --> 00:24:31,590
Sure.

414
00:24:36,905 --> 00:24:38,736
- This is silly, Ginger.
- Why?

415
00:24:38,940 --> 00:24:40,066
- It's Sunday.
- So?

416
00:24:40,308 --> 00:24:43,436
It's his day off.
He wants to spend it alone with you.

417
00:24:43,678 --> 00:24:45,441
He's alone with me plenty.

418
00:24:45,680 --> 00:24:49,116
If I'm gonna marry Chili, you're
gonna meet him sooner than later.

419
00:24:49,350 --> 00:24:51,181
I told him we'd show you the town.

420
00:24:51,386 --> 00:24:55,447
- Well, he won't want your sister around.
- Will you stop it?

421
00:24:56,124 --> 00:24:59,355
This city is so
beautifully European.

422
00:24:59,561 --> 00:25:01,461
Have you ever been abroad?

423
00:25:01,696 --> 00:25:03,186
- At all?
- No.

424
00:25:03,398 --> 00:25:06,526
We used to sail
from Saint-Tropez to Cannes...

425
00:25:06,734 --> 00:25:08,964
...and up the coast to Monaco.

426
00:25:09,470 --> 00:25:12,597
- It reminds me of the Mediterranean.
- There's Chili.

427
00:25:12,839 --> 00:25:14,636
- Which one?
- There.

428
00:25:14,875 --> 00:25:16,740
- Who's that with him?
- I don't know.

429
00:25:17,277 --> 00:25:18,904
- Chili.
- Hi.

430
00:25:19,112 --> 00:25:20,943
- Hi, hey.
- You look beautiful.

431
00:25:21,148 --> 00:25:23,082
- Oh, thanks.
- Yeah.

432
00:25:23,350 --> 00:25:25,113
- You smell good too.
- You're late.

433
00:25:25,352 --> 00:25:28,344
- Eddie. Nice to meet you.
- Hi. Ginger. Hi.

434
00:25:28,555 --> 00:25:29,613
This is Jasmine.

435
00:25:29,856 --> 00:25:31,915
- Jasmine, hi. I'm Eddie.
- This is Eddie.

436
00:25:32,125 --> 00:25:34,286
- Nice to meet you. Eddie.
- I'm Jasmine.

437
00:25:34,494 --> 00:25:36,155
- Hi.
- Ginger told me about you.

438
00:25:36,396 --> 00:25:38,626
Oh, all good, I hope.

439
00:25:38,865 --> 00:25:42,096
I gotta tell you, I was all set
to move in with your sister.

440
00:25:42,302 --> 00:25:45,965
Then she tells me that we gotta
postpone because her sister's in town.

441
00:25:46,173 --> 00:25:49,074
- He's joking.
- Well, I hope I didn't inconvenience you.

442
00:25:49,276 --> 00:25:50,470
It was an emergency.

443
00:25:50,944 --> 00:25:52,741
- No.
- Things happen. Right, Eddie?

444
00:25:52,946 --> 00:25:54,743
Could've happened to anybody.

445
00:25:54,948 --> 00:25:57,507
Told me you never been here,
don't know anybody...

446
00:25:57,750 --> 00:26:00,651
...so I brought along this
sad excuse for a blind date.

447
00:26:00,886 --> 00:26:03,650
- Best he could do on short notice.
- He works with me.

448
00:26:03,889 --> 00:26:05,151
I gotta get a beer.

449
00:26:05,391 --> 00:26:07,655
- You want a beer?
- Can I buy you a drink?

450
00:26:07,893 --> 00:26:11,021
- I have a drink, but thank you.
- I'm dropping dead of hunger.

451
00:26:11,263 --> 00:26:13,322
This place has the best clams.

452
00:26:13,532 --> 00:26:15,022
You like clams, Jasmine?

453
00:26:15,468 --> 00:26:17,163
No, no, no. I'm not hungry.

454
00:26:17,670 --> 00:26:20,662
What the hell are you drinking?
Let me see. What is this?

455
00:26:20,906 --> 00:26:22,032
- Is it vodka?
- Martini.

456
00:26:22,274 --> 00:26:24,432
This place has the best
clams in the city.

457
00:26:24,458 --> 00:26:25,962
The best are at Manero's.

458
00:26:26,145 --> 00:26:29,012
- You're nuts. They don't even compare.
- Who cares?

459
00:26:29,215 --> 00:26:32,776
This place is good too. They're fresh.
That's the thing with clams.

460
00:26:32,985 --> 00:26:35,977
You get a bad clam,
you'll wish you were never born.

461
00:26:36,188 --> 00:26:39,520
- So, what do you do, Jasmine?
- I told you, she just got here.

462
00:26:39,724 --> 00:26:41,555
- She's looking for a job.
- Yeah?

463
00:26:41,926 --> 00:26:44,360
I know a dentist who's
looking for help.

464
00:26:44,562 --> 00:26:46,621
- Oh, yeah?
- No, I'm actually thinking...

465
00:26:46,831 --> 00:26:49,231
- ... of going back to school.
- School?

466
00:26:50,235 --> 00:26:52,169
To study what?

467
00:26:53,705 --> 00:26:56,640
I don't know. I mean,
the biggest mistake I made...

468
00:26:56,841 --> 00:27:01,039
...was leaving college in my last
year and not completing my education.

469
00:27:01,246 --> 00:27:02,543
What would you be?

470
00:27:02,747 --> 00:27:04,339
An anthropologist.

471
00:27:05,050 --> 00:27:07,541
Really? Like digging up old fossils?

472
00:27:07,752 --> 00:27:09,219
That's an archaeologist.

473
00:27:09,454 --> 00:27:11,445
Ginger told me the whole story.

474
00:27:11,656 --> 00:27:13,146
That must be terrible, right?

475
00:27:13,358 --> 00:27:15,883
One minute you're on top
of the world, the next-

476
00:27:16,094 --> 00:27:18,358
- Guy turns out to be a crook.
- Yeah.

477
00:27:18,563 --> 00:27:20,963
Her husband, he owned racehorses.

478
00:27:21,166 --> 00:27:22,757
- Is that so?
- Yeah.

479
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:25,992
Oh, yes, yes, for a year or two...

480
00:27:26,203 --> 00:27:28,694
...Hal became quite obsessed
with thoroughbreds.

481
00:27:29,206 --> 00:27:31,367
So, what are you gonna study
in college?

482
00:27:31,575 --> 00:27:32,599
Let me guess.

483
00:27:33,343 --> 00:27:35,106
A nurse.

484
00:27:35,579 --> 00:27:37,672
Is that how I impress you?

485
00:27:37,881 --> 00:27:40,907
- A nurse?
- You got something against nurses?

486
00:27:41,118 --> 00:27:44,485
- My sister's a nurse.
- Nurses are very hot to go to bed with.

487
00:27:44,688 --> 00:27:47,851
They have extensive knowledge
of how the human body works.

488
00:27:48,058 --> 00:27:52,119
- Careful what you accuse my sister of.
- Just saying, I know a few good nurses.

489
00:27:52,362 --> 00:27:54,387
Chili, why don't you
change the subject?

490
00:27:54,598 --> 00:27:57,431
You think you're being charming,
but you're not.

491
00:27:57,634 --> 00:28:00,034
You always stare into
space like that?

492
00:28:00,938 --> 00:28:02,906
I had a friend who
used to do that...

493
00:28:03,107 --> 00:28:06,235
...but there was something wrong
with him. He was epileptic.

494
00:28:07,310 --> 00:28:09,801
I'm not epileptic.

495
00:28:10,813 --> 00:28:13,941
If you see the waitress,
I'd like another Stoli martini.

496
00:28:14,150 --> 00:28:16,516
- What are you gonna study?
- Leave her alone.

497
00:28:16,719 --> 00:28:19,950
- It's like the third time you asked.
- So? She hasn't answered.

498
00:28:20,156 --> 00:28:23,284
I don't know, but I'll be sure
to keep you informed.

499
00:28:23,526 --> 00:28:27,895
- Oh, okay, sorry. I'll back off.
- I'm sorry, I don't mean to be curt.

500
00:28:28,097 --> 00:28:31,328
I just don't know what I'm gonna do
with the rest of my life.

501
00:28:31,567 --> 00:28:34,900
- What do you wanna do?
- Why don't we take her to see the sights?

502
00:28:35,104 --> 00:28:38,938
Then back to my place. She likes vodka.
My buddy's just back from Russia.

503
00:28:39,142 --> 00:28:41,610
- Brought me this incredible vodka.
- Great idea.

504
00:28:41,811 --> 00:28:45,178
- You're gonna love my place.
- Yeah, let's go.

505
00:29:14,609 --> 00:29:17,806
- Wait till you try this vodka.
- All right, man.

506
00:29:18,013 --> 00:29:19,776
I wish my apartment had a garden.

507
00:29:19,981 --> 00:29:22,609
- We didn't take her inside Alcatraz.
- Thank you.

508
00:29:22,818 --> 00:29:26,811
- They got tours in there, Jasmine.
- Ginger said your ex-husband did time?

509
00:29:27,022 --> 00:29:30,458
He'd still be doing time if he
didn't hang himself in his cell.

510
00:29:30,659 --> 00:29:31,942
Really? Like with a belt?

511
00:29:31,968 --> 00:29:34,380
Well, it had to be a belt.
Or a bedsheet.

512
00:29:34,595 --> 00:29:36,028
- Could be a bedsheet.
- No.

513
00:29:36,230 --> 00:29:40,599
He managed to get a piece of rope.

514
00:29:41,602 --> 00:29:42,967
Plain rope.

515
00:29:43,170 --> 00:29:45,161
You can get anything
if you got juice.

516
00:29:45,372 --> 00:29:47,966
That's some way to go.
Strangle yourself to death?

517
00:29:48,175 --> 00:29:50,643
No, it wasn't strangulation.

518
00:29:50,845 --> 00:29:53,507
When you hang yourself,
your neck breaks.

519
00:29:53,714 --> 00:29:56,615
I wouldn't feel sorry for him.
He hurt a lot of people.

520
00:29:56,817 --> 00:29:59,843
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah, including me and Augie and her.

521
00:30:00,054 --> 00:30:03,217
A lot of people are under
the misapprehension you strangle...

522
00:30:03,424 --> 00:30:06,257
- ... but your neck snaps.
- Okay, we got it.

523
00:30:06,827 --> 00:30:08,761
He was a bad guy, you know?

524
00:30:08,996 --> 00:30:11,521
He lived like a big shot
on other people's money.

525
00:30:11,732 --> 00:30:15,131
- And he played around behind her back.
- No.

526
00:30:15,166 --> 00:30:18,531
- Jasmine, go and start your cooldown.
- Oh, good.

527
00:30:21,541 --> 00:30:22,940
- Hey, Jas.
- Yeah?

528
00:30:23,176 --> 00:30:26,077
I know you don't wanna go
to the Yankee game tonight.

529
00:30:26,279 --> 00:30:30,739
I'd go to any sporting event with you,
you know, but I just never got baseball.

530
00:30:30,950 --> 00:30:35,216
- I thought I'd ask Melanie. She's a fan.
- Oh, sure. God, she'll be thrilled.

531
00:30:35,421 --> 00:30:36,683
- Hey, Mel?
- Yeah?

532
00:30:36,890 --> 00:30:39,518
- You like baseball, right?
- I love baseball. Why?

533
00:30:39,726 --> 00:30:44,163
I got two season tickets behind
the Yankee dugout for tonight.

534
00:30:44,364 --> 00:30:47,197
I don't have anybody else to go with me.
Are you free?

535
00:30:47,400 --> 00:30:50,028
Absolutely, if you're sure
there's nobody else.

536
00:30:50,236 --> 00:30:51,396
No.

537
00:30:51,604 --> 00:30:54,732
- No, no, you'll do just fine.
- All right, thanks.

538
00:30:57,210 --> 00:30:59,110
- This is where you live? Nice.
- Yeah.

539
00:30:59,312 --> 00:31:02,542
- Hey, can you grab the groceries for me?
- Yeah.

540
00:31:08,820 --> 00:31:10,788
- I can get this one.
- Get them.

541
00:31:10,989 --> 00:31:13,287
- You got it? All right.
- I got it.

542
00:31:15,294 --> 00:31:17,387
- Oh, no.
- That's okay, don't worry.

543
00:31:17,596 --> 00:31:20,121
- No more vodka for you.
- I didn't have any vodka.

544
00:31:20,332 --> 00:31:22,596
- I didn't have no vodka.
- I know about you.

545
00:31:22,801 --> 00:31:25,133
Hey, hey, come here,
come here, come here.

546
00:31:25,337 --> 00:31:26,599
- Take it upstairs?
- Yes?

547
00:31:26,805 --> 00:31:27,931
- Yeah.
- All right.

548
00:31:28,440 --> 00:31:30,499
Eddie wants your phone number.

549
00:31:31,777 --> 00:31:33,745
- Why?
- I think he wants to call you.

550
00:31:33,946 --> 00:31:36,779
I think he wants to ask you out,
you know, for dinner.

551
00:31:36,982 --> 00:31:40,577
- Look, I'm busy at the moment.
- He's a terrific guy. Look at him.

552
00:31:40,786 --> 00:31:42,981
Well, why doesn't he ask me himself?

553
00:31:43,221 --> 00:31:46,121
Because he's shy, you know?
He thinks he's short.

554
00:31:48,225 --> 00:31:51,126
Look, I'm concentrating
on school, okay?

555
00:31:51,329 --> 00:31:53,160
- And getting a job.
- That's perfect.

556
00:31:53,364 --> 00:31:55,332
Right, he knows this dentist.

557
00:31:55,533 --> 00:31:58,434
No, I have no interest
in being a receptionist.

558
00:31:58,636 --> 00:32:00,968
What did you have in mind,
running a bank?

559
00:32:01,172 --> 00:32:04,938
- Is this what you wanted to talk about?
- And how long you're planning...

560
00:32:05,142 --> 00:32:06,479
...on staying with Ginger.

561
00:32:06,505 --> 00:32:08,830
Oh, right. It's just
till I find my feet.

562
00:32:09,013 --> 00:32:10,446
We have a lot of big plans.

563
00:32:10,648 --> 00:32:13,481
Don't worry, I'm not gonna ruin
any of your big plans.

564
00:32:13,684 --> 00:32:16,448
No one wants to get out of here
as fast as I do.

565
00:32:16,654 --> 00:32:19,851
I'm sure this is a big comedown
from what you're used to.

566
00:32:20,057 --> 00:32:23,618
It's fine.
It's- I'm grateful for her help.

567
00:32:23,828 --> 00:32:25,762
So you don't want Eddie to call you?

568
00:32:25,963 --> 00:32:29,398
No, I'm not ready to go out
at the moment.

569
00:32:30,633 --> 00:32:33,363
Ginger said
you had a nervous breakdown.

570
00:32:36,506 --> 00:32:38,167
She tends to be quite dramatic.

571
00:32:38,375 --> 00:32:41,003
Said you were in the street,
talking to yourself.

572
00:32:43,913 --> 00:32:47,713
You know, I don't think
that this is any of your business.

573
00:32:47,917 --> 00:32:52,081
No, but since I'm marrying her,
we don't have any secrets between us.

574
00:32:58,028 --> 00:33:00,087
- What did Chili want?
- Oh, nothing.

575
00:33:00,330 --> 00:33:04,391
His retarded boyfriend wanted a date,
but he was too shy to ask.

576
00:33:04,601 --> 00:33:08,332
- What do you think of Chili?
- He's very anxious to move in with you.

577
00:33:08,538 --> 00:33:10,733
Yeah, I know.
He's got the hots for me.

578
00:33:10,940 --> 00:33:12,430
Can I speak frankly?

579
00:33:12,674 --> 00:33:14,403
- You hate him?
- Yeah.

580
00:33:14,610 --> 00:33:17,101
I could tell you two
didn't hit it off.

581
00:33:17,346 --> 00:33:20,747
He's another version of Augie.
He's a loser.

582
00:33:20,949 --> 00:33:24,350
Hey, didn't I hear Eddie say he
knows a dentist looking for help?

583
00:33:24,553 --> 00:33:28,182
Oh, forget it! Jesus,
it's too menial!

584
00:33:28,390 --> 00:33:30,381
I'd go nuts.

585
00:33:31,460 --> 00:33:33,894
I wanna go back to school.

586
00:33:34,096 --> 00:33:39,966
I wanna get my degree and become,
you know, something substantial.

587
00:33:40,235 --> 00:33:43,102
I can't just do some mindless job.

588
00:33:43,338 --> 00:33:46,466
I was forced to take a job
selling shoes on Madison Avenue.

589
00:33:46,708 --> 00:33:49,541
Oh, so humiliating.

590
00:33:49,745 --> 00:33:53,442
Friends I'd had at dinner parties
at our apartment came in...

591
00:33:53,649 --> 00:33:57,607
...and I waited on them. I mean,
do you have any idea what that's like?

592
00:33:57,852 --> 00:34:01,481
You know, one minute,
you're hosting women...

593
00:34:01,722 --> 00:34:05,749
...and the next, you're measuring
their shoe size and fitting them.

594
00:34:06,294 --> 00:34:08,455
Erica Bishop came into the store.

595
00:34:08,663 --> 00:34:12,622
She saw me
and was so embarrassed for me...

596
00:34:12,867 --> 00:34:16,064
...she slipped out
thinking I didn't see her.

597
00:34:16,404 --> 00:34:19,373
I saw you, Erica!

598
00:34:21,375 --> 00:34:23,309
Are you okay?

599
00:34:24,412 --> 00:34:26,972
Hey, you got great taste.

600
00:34:27,181 --> 00:34:31,743
Maybe you could do something
in fashion.

601
00:34:31,953 --> 00:34:33,386
Or designing. Yeah?

602
00:34:34,589 --> 00:34:36,819
- Yeah, that's true.
- Yeah.

603
00:34:37,024 --> 00:34:40,117
Everyone used to say
I'd make a good interior decorator.

604
00:34:41,595 --> 00:34:44,120
There's courses,
but, you know, they cost money.

605
00:34:44,331 --> 00:34:48,324
No, Eve Logan
got her decorator's license online.

606
00:34:48,535 --> 00:34:50,526
On a computer?

607
00:34:50,770 --> 00:34:52,135
I guess you could, but-

608
00:34:52,339 --> 00:34:55,706
Yeah, I'm so computer illiterate.

609
00:34:56,610 --> 00:34:58,805
But I could take a
class in computers.

610
00:34:59,012 --> 00:35:03,711
And then when I can handle a computer,
then I can study decorating online.

611
00:35:03,950 --> 00:35:08,284
- That sounds too complicated.
- Why is your reaction always negative?

612
00:35:08,488 --> 00:35:10,115
I'm just saying.

613
00:35:10,323 --> 00:35:12,689
You know, first you gotta
learn computers...

614
00:35:12,926 --> 00:35:15,520
...and then go for a decorator's
license online.

615
00:35:15,729 --> 00:35:18,926
You're afraid I'll
stay here too long.

616
00:35:19,132 --> 00:35:20,861
No, you know-

617
00:35:21,067 --> 00:35:24,365
Just all those courses,
they cost money.

618
00:35:25,437 --> 00:35:29,965
You'll work out here. It's mostly phones
and keeping my appointments straight.

619
00:35:30,176 --> 00:35:33,236
There's the follow-up cards,
which I explained...

620
00:35:33,479 --> 00:35:36,175
...and the notices for cleanings.

621
00:35:36,682 --> 00:35:38,513
Any questions?

622
00:35:39,552 --> 00:35:42,214
Tell Dr. Flicker it's an emergency.

623
00:35:42,454 --> 00:35:45,753
- Come on, come on.
- Yes?

624
00:35:46,859 --> 00:35:47,883
What?

625
00:35:48,093 --> 00:35:50,061
Yes, a cancellation.

626
00:35:50,262 --> 00:35:52,890
Oh, you want to cancel.

627
00:35:53,098 --> 00:35:54,565
- When?
- Please.

628
00:35:54,767 --> 00:35:58,498
Wait, wait, wait. You said the 24th.

629
00:35:58,704 --> 00:36:00,535
My husband has an abscess.

630
00:36:00,973 --> 00:36:04,238
Can you just put someone on
who speaks better English?

631
00:36:04,476 --> 00:36:09,037
The software interface
is what provides you, the user...

632
00:36:09,247 --> 00:36:12,705
...the ability to control
the hardware, the computer.

633
00:36:12,917 --> 00:36:14,578
Okay, that's the operating.

634
00:36:14,786 --> 00:36:18,722
The operating system
gives you that ability.

635
00:36:18,923 --> 00:36:20,891
I need an appointment in two weeks.

636
00:36:26,798 --> 00:36:29,426
Is the 10th good for you?

637
00:36:29,634 --> 00:36:32,603
The 10th. Yes, fine.

638
00:36:32,804 --> 00:36:35,068
Oh, better make it the 12th.

639
00:36:35,273 --> 00:36:38,436
- Oh, we're all booked on the 12th.
- Okay.

640
00:36:38,643 --> 00:36:39,940
Make it the 14th.

641
00:36:40,645 --> 00:36:42,442
- The 14th?
- Oh, no.

642
00:36:42,647 --> 00:36:44,740
Is 3 good on the 9th?

643
00:36:44,949 --> 00:36:46,917
Or noon on the 11 th?

644
00:36:47,118 --> 00:36:51,145
Can you just settle on a time, please?
Just pick a time.

645
00:36:52,022 --> 00:36:54,650
Remember the yoga class.

646
00:36:56,827 --> 00:36:58,886
Deep breath.

647
00:36:59,763 --> 00:37:01,822
Breathe deeply.

648
00:37:02,833 --> 00:37:06,792
All right, deep breath.

649
00:37:09,840 --> 00:37:12,934
If you take a deep breath,
you can smell the honeysuckle.

650
00:37:13,143 --> 00:37:16,078
- Beautiful. Make a great perfume.
- It would.

651
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:18,805
- Your polo pony's in great shape.
- Thank you.

652
00:37:19,049 --> 00:37:21,347
- No, I have never seen a polo match.
- Really?

653
00:37:21,585 --> 00:37:25,954
My husband's a fanatic. Not to say
he's good at it, but it keeps him busy.

654
00:37:26,156 --> 00:37:27,680
We got a flight to catch.

655
00:37:27,924 --> 00:37:30,449
Hal's taking Danny to Augusta
for the Masters.

656
00:37:30,661 --> 00:37:33,186
They're golf degenerates.
I'll be home alone.

657
00:37:33,430 --> 00:37:36,091
- We'll be back in three days.
- Did we tell you?

658
00:37:36,299 --> 00:37:38,665
- Danny was first in his class at Harvard.
- No.

659
00:37:38,868 --> 00:37:40,062
- Yes.
- Congratulations.

660
00:37:40,269 --> 00:37:41,759
- Thanks.
- He's a math genius.

661
00:37:41,971 --> 00:37:45,429
He's the genius. Dad did a guest
lecture at the business school...

662
00:37:45,641 --> 00:37:48,007
...and everyone said
it was the best lecture.

663
00:37:48,210 --> 00:37:51,145
Naturally I became an instant
celebrity on campus.

664
00:37:51,347 --> 00:37:54,145
Hey, I need your signature
on these, baby.

665
00:37:55,885 --> 00:38:00,515
Be careful. Don't get hit by a golf ball.
That's how Ray Becker died.

666
00:38:00,723 --> 00:38:04,022
You know, a little blue bruise
on his temple.

667
00:38:13,736 --> 00:38:17,536
What are you always studying
in your spare time?

668
00:38:17,740 --> 00:38:20,333
Well, I'm trying to learn
to use a computer.

669
00:38:20,542 --> 00:38:23,841
I wanna study interior
design online.

670
00:38:24,045 --> 00:38:26,172
Oh, you wanna be a decorator?

671
00:38:26,381 --> 00:38:28,508
Yeah, it's where my
strongest gifts are.

672
00:38:28,717 --> 00:38:31,550
You know, I have a natural flair
for space and color...

673
00:38:31,753 --> 00:38:34,551
...and an eye for choosing
soft furnishings.

674
00:38:34,756 --> 00:38:38,988
It's very commendable, but I can't
really have you studying on work time...

675
00:38:39,194 --> 00:38:41,560
...if it interferes
with the business at hand.

676
00:38:41,763 --> 00:38:44,357
Yes. I'm sorry.
It won't happen again.

677
00:38:44,566 --> 00:38:46,625
Please, see that it doesn't.

678
00:38:48,770 --> 00:38:54,572
- I was gonna ask you a question.
- Yes?

679
00:38:56,211 --> 00:38:59,271
Would you have a drink with me?

680
00:38:59,848 --> 00:39:01,577
A drink?

681
00:39:03,150 --> 00:39:05,015
I'd love it if you could.

682
00:39:05,552 --> 00:39:08,282
Well, it would have
to be a quick one...

683
00:39:08,522 --> 00:39:12,253
...because, you know,
I'm meeting my boyfriend for dinner.

684
00:39:16,063 --> 00:39:17,223
I was just saying...

685
00:39:17,431 --> 00:39:21,060
...you can tell an awful lot about
people when you look in their mouths.

686
00:39:21,268 --> 00:39:25,432
Are they conscientious?
Are they disciplined? Are they vain?

687
00:39:25,672 --> 00:39:28,436
Or careless?
You have to know what to look for.

688
00:39:28,675 --> 00:39:31,439
Do you have the time?
I have to keep an eye on it.

689
00:39:31,678 --> 00:39:32,702
I've got homework.

690
00:39:32,913 --> 00:39:37,907
This computer thing is proving a
little more difficult than I imagined.

691
00:39:38,118 --> 00:39:42,714
It's funny, really, because I used to
be a straight-A student in college.

692
00:39:42,923 --> 00:39:46,915
You know, but they say every year,
millions of brain cells just die off.

693
00:39:47,126 --> 00:39:49,185
You have good teeth.

694
00:39:50,997 --> 00:39:53,192
I'm sure you get
many compliments on them.

695
00:39:53,399 --> 00:39:56,061
- Well, thank you.
- Yeah.

696
00:39:56,335 --> 00:39:59,566
You know,
