That trainer he used to take
to baseball games.

1375
01:17:40,546 --> 01:17:42,672
- Oh, my God.
- You know how many people...

1376
01:17:42,914 --> 01:17:46,509
...have said to me he's doing his lawyer,
the Chinese dragon lady?

1377
01:17:46,718 --> 01:17:49,551
- Can we get the waiter? I need a drink.
- Yes. Waiter.

1378
01:17:49,788 --> 01:17:51,016
- Yes, ma'am?
- This again.

1379
01:17:51,223 --> 01:17:53,191
- Right away. Thank you.
- Absolutely.

1380
01:18:15,947 --> 01:18:17,437
Hello?

1381
01:18:18,016 --> 01:18:20,041
Yeah, is Al there?

1382
01:18:20,519 --> 01:18:23,079
Al Munsinger, yeah.

1383
01:18:25,322 --> 01:18:28,883
I know he works
in the Audio Department, yeah.

1384
01:18:29,493 --> 01:18:31,222
Yeah, I'll hold.

1385
01:18:34,265 --> 01:18:35,892
Hello?

1386
01:18:36,467 --> 01:18:39,265
Al Munsinger, yes.

1387
01:18:39,870 --> 01:18:42,737
Al, where the hell are you?

1388
01:18:43,474 --> 01:18:44,839
What?

1389
01:18:45,609 --> 01:18:48,669
What? I don't get it.
Why couldn't you come?

1390
01:18:54,051 --> 01:18:56,076
Who found out what?

1391
01:18:58,122 --> 01:18:59,919
Who's Ellen?

1392
01:19:09,032 --> 01:19:10,431
Yeah, I-

1393
01:19:10,633 --> 01:19:13,227
I didn't understand you had a wife.

1394
01:19:15,638 --> 01:19:17,105
No.

1395
01:19:17,807 --> 01:19:19,934
No, you never said.

1396
01:19:35,325 --> 01:19:37,316
My mother was very impressed
with you.

1397
01:19:37,560 --> 01:19:39,755
- Really?
- Yeah. You two had a discussion...

1398
01:19:39,963 --> 01:19:42,898
- ... about her collection of pewter.
- Yes. I love pewter.

1399
01:19:43,099 --> 01:19:46,068
Hal used to have his beer
out of a pewter mug.

1400
01:19:46,536 --> 01:19:47,628
And your dad?

1401
01:19:47,837 --> 01:19:51,830
My dad can be very critical sometimes,
but he was very taken with you.

1402
01:19:52,575 --> 01:19:55,600
Well, don't worry,
I won't pick out too big a stone.

1403
01:19:55,811 --> 01:19:58,245
Yeah, nothing larger
than the Hope diamond.

1404
01:19:58,447 --> 01:20:00,677
Hey, Jasmine.

1405
01:20:01,984 --> 01:20:04,851
What? You don't remember me?

1406
01:20:05,654 --> 01:20:08,623
Of course I remember you.
What a surprise.

1407
01:20:09,558 --> 01:20:11,788
Yeah, surprise, surprise, huh?

1408
01:20:12,561 --> 01:20:14,756
This is Augie. Dwight.

1409
01:20:14,963 --> 01:20:16,794
- Dwight, hi.
- How you doing?

1410
01:20:16,999 --> 01:20:18,660
I was married to her sister.

1411
01:20:19,301 --> 01:20:21,098
- Okay.
- Years ago. Years.

1412
01:20:21,303 --> 01:20:24,329
Wasn't that many years.
She makes it sound ancient.

1413
01:20:24,573 --> 01:20:28,168
Congratulations. Ginger said
you got a new job up in Alaska.

1414
01:20:29,678 --> 01:20:32,511
I could've had my own company
if it wasn't for you...

1415
01:20:32,714 --> 01:20:36,774
- ... and that crook you married.
- I don't think it's the time and place.

1416
01:20:36,984 --> 01:20:41,683
Oh, really? You think I wanna lay oil
pipe way the hell up there in Alaska?

1417
01:20:41,889 --> 01:20:43,288
I got no money.

1418
01:20:43,491 --> 01:20:46,858
Christ, can't you put this behind you
and move on? I've moved on.

1419
01:20:47,094 --> 01:20:51,224
- Take it easy. I don't know who you are-
- Right, you don't, so stay out of it.

1420
01:20:51,833 --> 01:20:53,095
I saw your son.

1421
01:20:54,235 --> 01:20:56,669
Yeah, that's right, Danny.
Remember him?

1422
01:20:57,205 --> 01:21:01,539
Lives across the bridge in Oakland,
works at a music store. Antonio's.

1423
01:21:02,109 --> 01:21:05,101
He's doing pretty good.
He's married.

1424
01:21:05,646 --> 01:21:08,171
I think he's finally
over Hal's suicide.

1425
01:21:08,749 --> 01:21:11,047
Danny's in Oakland?

1426
01:21:11,252 --> 01:21:15,052
Let me tell you something,
Jeanette, Jasmine...

1427
01:21:15,256 --> 01:21:18,225
...whatever it is
you call yourself these days.

1428
01:21:18,426 --> 01:21:20,393
Some people...

1429
01:21:20,627 --> 01:21:24,119
...they don't put things behind
so easily.

1430
01:21:32,138 --> 01:21:33,867
You have a son?

1431
01:21:34,774 --> 01:21:39,143
Yes, I have a son. He's not- Biologically
he's not my son. He's my step-

1432
01:21:39,346 --> 01:21:41,644
- Hal's suicide?
- I can explain it all later.

1433
01:21:41,848 --> 01:21:44,681
- Can we just-?
- Not until you tell me what's going on.

1434
01:21:44,885 --> 01:21:46,716
- Not in the street.
- I want to know.

1435
01:21:46,920 --> 01:21:49,582
- I know. We'll go somewhere quiet.
- Get in the car.

1436
01:21:49,789 --> 01:21:52,758
- Don't talk to me in that tone of voice.
- Okay.

1437
01:21:57,797 --> 01:22:01,358
Of course we can't get married!
You lied to me up and down the line!

1438
01:22:01,568 --> 01:22:04,195
- No, I wanted to tell you.
- Are you delusional?

1439
01:22:04,403 --> 01:22:06,303
Didn't you think I'd find out?

1440
01:22:06,538 --> 01:22:09,598
- What were you thinking?
- I don't know what I was thinking.

1441
01:22:09,808 --> 01:22:12,936
Everything happened in the past.
You and I loved each other.

1442
01:22:13,178 --> 01:22:14,805
What? That it would just vanish?

1443
01:22:15,047 --> 01:22:18,778
Didn't you think I would find out,
if not today, eventually?

1444
01:22:18,984 --> 01:22:23,546
Like after we were married? Is that what
you wanted, to wait until it was too late?

1445
01:22:23,756 --> 01:22:26,884
For your future plans where you
needed the appropriate wife?

1446
01:22:27,092 --> 01:22:30,584
I won't say it wouldn't be an issue,
but that you could stand by...

1447
01:22:30,796 --> 01:22:34,323
- ... deceive me until I married you-
- No, you mean till I trapped you.

1448
01:22:34,566 --> 01:22:36,732
Your ethical behavior
is equal to your ex.

1449
01:22:36,758 --> 01:22:38,823
I wasn't deceiving you.
I loved you.

1450
01:22:39,004 --> 01:22:42,770
- I found out by chance, by sheer chance.
- Okay, if it's over, it's over.

1451
01:22:42,975 --> 01:22:46,411
I get it. You're not marrying me.
I brought everything on myself.

1452
01:22:46,612 --> 01:22:50,809
I've only got myself to blame.
I did it to myself again, as usual.

1453
01:22:51,015 --> 01:22:53,643
You and your stupid
little French whore.

1454
01:22:53,851 --> 01:22:56,164
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

1455
01:22:56,190 --> 01:22:57,676
Let me out of the car.

1456
01:22:57,855 --> 01:23:00,585
- Let me out of the car.
- How are you gonna get home?

1457
01:23:00,792 --> 01:23:03,727
I'm not going home. Let me out.
Let me out of the car!

1458
01:23:25,483 --> 01:23:28,850
Hey, remember to tell her
when she gets here, okay?

1459
01:23:29,053 --> 01:23:30,884
Believe me, she won't care.

1460
01:23:31,122 --> 01:23:33,851
- She is half out the door.
- Yeah, well...

1461
01:23:34,057 --> 01:23:36,025
I didn't start out not liking her.

1462
01:23:36,259 --> 01:23:39,251
I think she had it in for me
from the moment she met me.

1463
01:23:40,063 --> 01:23:41,291
Well, I like you.

1464
01:23:41,498 --> 01:23:44,399
Now, that's what counts,
not how she feels about you.

1465
01:23:44,634 --> 01:23:47,296
You know, I'm sick of her
calling you a loser...

1466
01:23:47,504 --> 01:23:50,837
...or always pushing me
to find a better man.

1467
01:23:51,041 --> 01:23:54,169
You know, in my book,
you're no loser.

1468
01:23:54,378 --> 01:23:57,370
You're twice the guy I met at
the party she dragged me to.

1469
01:23:57,581 --> 01:23:59,378
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

1470
01:23:59,583 --> 01:24:01,141
- Well, I love you.
- I know.

1471
01:24:01,351 --> 01:24:04,059
I love the boys. I
think they love me too.

1472
01:24:04,085 --> 01:24:04,903
They do.

1473
01:24:05,088 --> 01:24:09,491
- When I thought I lost you-
- You didn't lose me, baby.

1474
01:24:09,693 --> 01:24:11,888
I almost lost you.

1475
01:24:39,321 --> 01:24:42,347
Is this what you gave up
everything for?

1476
01:24:42,558 --> 01:24:46,255
To sell secondhand
musical instruments?

1477
01:24:47,696 --> 01:24:51,132
I asked Augie not to tell you
where I was.

1478
01:24:53,102 --> 01:24:54,831
Why?

1479
01:24:56,338 --> 01:24:58,329
What happened?

1480
01:24:59,040 --> 01:25:01,770
Why did you disappear like that
and never contact me?

1481
01:25:01,976 --> 01:25:05,468
I couldn't find you
when I needed you.

1482
01:25:06,081 --> 01:25:10,950
I know the whole story, I found it out,
so don't act so surprised.

1483
01:25:18,793 --> 01:25:21,853
Are you having an affair
with Lisette Boudreau?

1484
01:25:22,363 --> 01:25:24,661
Oh, Jasmine,
I can't do this without a drink.

1485
01:25:24,899 --> 01:25:27,800
No, don't tap dance.
You never went to Chicago.

1486
01:25:28,002 --> 01:25:30,368
You took the Jordans' au pair
to Paris.

1487
01:25:30,572 --> 01:25:32,802
I know what's been going on.

1488
01:25:33,174 --> 01:25:36,769
- Can we talk about this, please?
- You bet we can talk about it.

1489
01:25:36,978 --> 01:25:38,468
Can you do it calmly?

1490
01:25:38,680 --> 01:25:42,309
I wanna talk to you about what's
going on, but you're always so-

1491
01:25:42,517 --> 01:25:44,108
How do you expect me to react?

1492
01:25:44,318 --> 01:25:46,809
You've been sleeping
with other women for years.

1493
01:25:47,020 --> 01:25:51,081
I mean, Raylene,
your secretary, our trainer.

1494
01:25:51,291 --> 01:25:53,816
- Amy.
- This is different.

1495
01:25:54,027 --> 01:25:55,927
This is serious.

1496
01:25:56,163 --> 01:25:58,290
Lisette and I are in love.

1497
01:25:59,166 --> 01:26:01,134
Wha-? What?

1498
01:26:01,435 --> 01:26:02,766
Are you crazy?

1499
01:26:02,970 --> 01:26:07,031
I'm sorry, but I need you to hear what
I'm saying. Lisette and I are in love.

1500
01:26:07,708 --> 01:26:10,802
What does that mean?
What does that stupidity even mean?

1501
01:26:11,011 --> 01:26:14,947
It means that we are making plans
for the future together.

1502
01:26:15,149 --> 01:26:17,447
I'm sorry.
I'm having trouble understanding.

1503
01:26:17,651 --> 01:26:21,018
I know this comes as a shock,
but I have to be honest with you.

1504
01:26:21,221 --> 01:26:24,622
You wanna be honest.
That's the biggest joke of all.

1505
01:26:24,825 --> 01:26:26,951
I've had casual
flirtations in the past.

1506
01:26:27,160 --> 01:26:29,993
They didn't mean anything until now.
This is different.

1507
01:26:30,196 --> 01:26:34,496
Are you out of your mind?
She is a teenager, for chrissake.

1508
01:26:34,700 --> 01:26:37,362
She's an au pair.
I mean, are you crazy?

1509
01:26:37,570 --> 01:26:39,885
Christ, this is hard
for me to tell you!

1510
01:26:39,911 --> 01:26:42,055
It's hard for you?
What about me?

1511
01:26:42,241 --> 01:26:44,141
This is so humiliating for me.

1512
01:26:44,343 --> 01:26:47,870
I mean, it is bad enough that everyone
knows you've been unfaithful.

1513
01:26:48,080 --> 01:26:51,481
But to throw me away for this
stupid-looking little French-

1514
01:26:51,684 --> 01:26:54,517
- I will take very good care of you.
- I'm sorry.

1515
01:26:54,720 --> 01:26:58,156
I can't breathe. I can't breathe.

1516
01:26:58,357 --> 01:27:01,053
I don't know what I'm-
What am I doing here?

1517
01:27:01,260 --> 01:27:05,253
Oh, God, this is unacceptable.
This is not gonna happen.

1518
01:27:05,498 --> 01:27:07,989
You're not going anywhere.
This is unacceptable.

1519
01:27:08,201 --> 01:27:11,966
- Jasmine, you're having a tantrum.
- Don't you touch me!

1520
01:27:12,170 --> 01:27:15,071
- Don't you touch me!
- You are having a tantrum.

1521
01:27:15,273 --> 01:27:17,764
Stop, stop.

1522
01:27:18,009 --> 01:27:20,705
- What am I doing here?
- Pull yourself together.

1523
01:27:21,279 --> 01:27:23,247
- I can't-
- Jasmine.

1524
01:27:26,484 --> 01:27:30,079
When you calm down, we can talk
like two civilized adults...

1525
01:27:30,288 --> 01:27:32,882
...about the arrangements
we have to make.

1526
01:27:45,870 --> 01:27:48,532
Until then I'm gonna
check into a hotel.

1527
01:27:55,946 --> 01:28:00,815
What am I doing here?
What am I doing here?

1528
01:28:12,763 --> 01:28:17,132
Hello.
Yes, I want the number of the FBI.

1529
01:28:17,901 --> 01:28:19,766
Can you connect me?

1530
01:28:21,338 --> 01:28:23,329
The FBI.

1531
01:28:23,807 --> 01:28:25,968
- Mr. Francis?
- Yes?

1532
01:28:26,176 --> 01:28:27,803
- Hal Francis?
- Yes.

1533
01:28:28,045 --> 01:28:31,105
I'm sorry, sir,
we have a warrant for your arrest.

1534
01:28:31,448 --> 01:28:33,780
- What?
- We have a warrant for your arrest.

1535
01:28:33,984 --> 01:28:36,452
- Is this some kind of a joke?
- No, sir.

1536
01:28:36,654 --> 01:28:39,816
- It's best if you come with us now.
- Under arrest for what?

1537
01:28:40,056 --> 01:28:42,616
Sir, come with us now.
We'll settle this downtown.

1538
01:28:42,825 --> 01:28:45,055
- Do you have a warrant?
- I do.

1539
01:28:46,162 --> 01:28:47,595
- Gonna handcuff me?
- We are.

1540
01:28:47,797 --> 01:28:51,130
- I wanna talk to my lawyer.
- You'll be able to call your lawyer.

1541
01:28:51,334 --> 01:28:54,269
But we'll warn you,
you have the right to remain silent.

1542
01:28:54,470 --> 01:28:57,268
Anything you say can be held
against you in court.

1543
01:28:57,473 --> 01:28:59,338
- Okay, okay, let's go.
- Let's go.

1544
01:28:59,575 --> 01:29:03,102
Jesus Christ Almighty.

1545
01:29:03,780 --> 01:29:08,649
- What am I being arrested for?
- We can discuss this downtown, sir.

1546
01:29:11,354 --> 01:29:16,018
As disillusioned as I was with him,
I hated you more.

1547
01:29:19,095 --> 01:29:22,689
The moment I did what I did,
I regretted it.

1548
01:29:23,398 --> 01:29:26,526
I don't wanna discuss it.
It's past. It's over.

1549
01:29:26,735 --> 01:29:29,329
You can't take back that phone call.

1550
01:29:31,173 --> 01:29:33,403
I need you, Danny.

1551
01:29:34,676 --> 01:29:38,544
I don't wanna see you, Jasmine.
I want the past past.

1552
01:29:38,747 --> 01:29:42,706
I've become a different person,
thanks to my wife. I'm off drugs.

1553
01:29:42,918 --> 01:29:46,615
Just, please, don't
spoil everything.

1554
01:29:46,822 --> 01:29:49,655
Just get out of my life
so I can move on.

1555
01:29:51,893 --> 01:29:53,622
Definitely.

1556
01:29:55,664 --> 01:29:56,722
- Hey.
- Hey.

1557
01:29:56,932 --> 01:29:59,924
Hey, have some champagne.

1558
01:30:00,635 --> 01:30:03,399
Chili brought some
over to celebrate.

1559
01:30:03,638 --> 01:30:05,662
We're back together.

1560
01:30:07,007 --> 01:30:09,908
I'm sorry,
I'm not in a celebratory mood.

1561
01:30:10,144 --> 01:30:13,341
I don't think I'd find that news
anything to celebrate about.

1562
01:30:13,547 --> 01:30:16,539
Hey, come on, Jasmine,
let's not dig at each other, okay?

1563
01:30:16,751 --> 01:30:19,652
I'm moving in, and she tells me
you found a rich husband.

1564
01:30:19,854 --> 01:30:22,345
- Gonna be a big shot in Washington.
- We made up.

1565
01:30:22,556 --> 01:30:26,754
- Yeah, she begged for my forgiveness.
- And he cried like a baby and apologized.

1566
01:30:26,961 --> 01:30:31,898
- I didn't cry.
- Bullshit. You cry all the time.

1567
01:30:32,099 --> 01:30:34,260
But we're moving in.

1568
01:30:34,468 --> 01:30:38,370
It's something we planned for a long time
and maybe if we'd just done it-

1569
01:30:38,572 --> 01:30:41,063
Oh, for chrissake.

1570
01:30:41,275 --> 01:30:43,743
What's wrong with your self-esteem?

1571
01:30:43,944 --> 01:30:47,937
There's men who'd never think about
ripping the phone out of the wall.

1572
01:30:48,182 --> 01:30:51,708
Hey, leave him alone.
You're always picking on him.

1573
01:30:51,918 --> 01:30:53,818
No, you choose losers, okay?

1574
01:30:54,053 --> 01:30:56,317
Because that's what you think
you deserve.

1575
01:30:56,556 --> 01:31:00,925
That's why you're living like this and
that's why you'll never have a better life.

1576
01:31:01,428 --> 01:31:03,328
I'm- I'm living-

1577
01:31:03,563 --> 01:31:09,297
I'm living like this because you
married the biggest loser of all...

1578
01:31:09,502 --> 01:31:11,800
...and went your own sweet way...

1579
01:31:12,005 --> 01:31:17,568
...while he pissed away my one big
chance to make a better life.

1580
01:31:17,777 --> 01:31:20,268
Come on, let's not ruin
our celebration, okay?

1581
01:31:20,480 --> 01:31:24,143
Come on, she's happy, we're happy.
Let's let sleeping dogs lie.

1582
01:31:24,350 --> 01:31:27,808
He's right. I'm not gonna be drawn
into defending myself...

1583
01:31:28,021 --> 01:31:31,855
...when all I wanted to do
was bring you in on a good deal.

1584
01:31:34,026 --> 01:31:36,995
I'm moving out of this place today.

1585
01:31:37,496 --> 01:31:39,657
I just gotta get myself together.

1586
01:31:39,865 --> 01:31:44,359
Dwight asked me to move in with
him, as I expected he would.

1587
01:31:44,603 --> 01:31:46,764
He wants me to finish
decorating his home.

1588
01:31:46,972 --> 01:31:49,497
Then we'll marry
and we'll move in together.

1589
01:31:49,741 --> 01:31:52,642
He's one of these men
who's lost without a woman.

1590
01:31:52,845 --> 01:31:55,837
It has to be the right woman,
who's a plus for his career.

1591
01:31:56,048 --> 01:32:00,485
And I have the social skills
required for his future in politics.

1592
01:32:00,853 --> 01:32:04,846
For the next few years,
we'll be living in Vienna.

1593
01:32:05,324 --> 01:32:08,521
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I'm gonna take a shower.

1594
01:32:08,760 --> 01:32:10,557
I'll send for my luggage.

1595
01:32:13,899 --> 01:32:18,528
I was pretty angry at some of the things
she said, but I kept it on the inside.

1596
01:32:19,670 --> 01:32:24,573
I'm tired of her knocking you.
You know?

1597
01:32:32,984 --> 01:32:35,817
Don't even think about taking
that last slice of pizza.

1598
01:32:36,020 --> 01:32:39,581
- What? Why?
